OL,3,CMetal detectorist reunites WWI medal
OL,4,Cwith family of soldier
OL,6,FA metal detectorist who uncovered a
OL,7,FFirst World War service medal has
OL,8,Fmanaged to track down the soldier's
OL,9,Fgreat niece and reunite her with the
OL,10,Fsentimental item.
OL,12,FStephen Brame discovered the silver
OL,13,Fmedal while detecting in a field in
OL,14,FAccrington, Lancashire, on Armistice
OL,15,Fday 2023.
OL,17,FAt first, he thought it was a George V
OL,18,Fsilver coin, but it was not until he
OL,19,Fcleaned it up and did some research
OL,20,Fthat he discovered it was a service
OL,21,Fmedal.
