OL,3,CMetal detectorist reunites WWI medal
OL,4,Cwith family of soldier
OL,6,FStephen said: "Honestly, I dug the
OL,7,Fhole and what came out was what I
OL,8,Fthought it was a silver coin.
OL,10,F"It was only when I got home, that I
OL,11,Fcleaned it up and realised it was a
OL,12,Fmedal. It was unbelievable really, to
OL,13,Factually find a medal on Armistice
OL,14,Fday."
OL,16,FAfter some research, Stephen and an
OL,17,Farchaeologist discovered the medal
OL,18,Fbelonged to Private Nicholas
OL,19,FFarnworth, a soldier who served with
OL,20,Fthe East Lancashire Regiment during
OL,21,Fthe First World War.
